---
import HubLayout from '../layouts/HubLayout.astro';
---

<HubLayout title="Privacy Policy — MyToolboxHub" description="Privacy policy for MyToolboxHub. All tools run 100% client-side. We do not collect, store, or transmit your data.">
  <div class="relative pt-8 pb-16 sm:pt-12 sm:pb-24 overflow-hidden mt-6 sm:mt-10 mb-12 sm:mb-16">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute bottom-1/4 left-1/3 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-accent/6 rounded-full blur-[100px]"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
      
      <!-- Heading -->
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-text-primary mb-4">
          Privacy <span class="text-accent">Policy</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Effective Date: June 15, 2026. Your privacy is not a policy here — it's our technical architecture.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Glass Card Content -->
      <div class="glass p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-2xl space-y-8 prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded-full"></span>
            1. Client-Side Execution Guarantee
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed text-sm">
            MyToolboxHub is engineered as a static web application. Every tool, calculation, conversion, formatting, or generation is executed entirely inside your web browser. 
          </p>
          <div class="bg-surface/50 border border-border-subtle p-4 rounded-xl text-xs text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-text-primary block mb-1">How it works:</strong>
            When you enter a color string, parse a JSON object, decode a JSON Web Token, or generate a password, all processing logic is handled by JavaScript compiling locally inside your browser process. No input payload is ever uploaded, sent, or routed to our servers.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded-full"></span>
            2. Information We Do Not Collect
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed text-sm">
            Because of our client-side design, we do not collect:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm text-text-secondary space-y-2">
            <li>Any inputs or content you paste, type, upload, or process.</li>
            <li>IP addresses, device identifiers, browser types, or user-agent details linked to your input payloads.</li>
            <li>No database logs of processed strings, keys, or records exist.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded-full"></span>
            3. Local Browser Storage
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed text-sm">
            Some utility tools may use your browser's local storage (such as <code class="text-accent bg-surface px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono">localStorage</code>) to store your preferred settings, history, or configurations so they persist between visits. This data remains completely local to your browser profile, and you can clear it at any time by clearing your browser's site data.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded-full"></span>
            4. Analytics
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed text-sm">
            We use a privacy-friendly, self-hosted version of Plausible Analytics to gather aggregate, non-personal usage statistics (e.g., page views, popular tools) to help us improve the service. No cookies are stored, and no personally identifiable information (PII) is tracked.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-accent rounded-full"></span>
            5. Contact Information
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed text-sm">
            If you have questions about our zero-data client-side structure, please reach out to us at <a href="mailto:privacy@mytoolboxhub.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">privacy@mytoolboxhub.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</HubLayout>
